**Summary of what was implemented:**

- **`auth/apikey.go`** — 7 authenticated API endpoints:
  - `POST /auth/api-keys` — Create key (32-byte crypto/rand, "bos_" prefix, SHA-256 hash stored)
  - `GET /auth/api-keys` — List keys (never exposes hash or full key)
  - `POST /auth/api-keys/:id/reset` — Reset key (new key, same ID)
  - `DELETE /auth/api-keys/:id` — Revoke key (sets status=revoked)
  - `POST /auth/api-keys/:id/ips` — Add IP/CIDR to whitelist
  - `DELETE /auth/api-keys/:id/ips` — Remove IP from whitelist
  - `GET /auth/api-keys/:id/ips` — List IP whitelist
  - All enforce ownership (`user_id` match) with admin override

- **`auth/auth_test.go`** — 5 new tests all passing:
  - TestAPIKeyCreate, TestAPIKeyListNeverExposesHash, TestAPIKeyReset, TestAPIKeyRevoked, TestIPWhitelist
